<head>DRUG</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>MEDICINE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">藥</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SUBSTANCE USED FOR CURING OR PREVENTING DISEASES.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for medicine is yào 藥, but originally this word referred specifically to herbal medicine.</p>
<p>2. Yuē 葯 is a specific word for the leaves of the bái zhǐ 白芷 aromatic herb.</p>
<p>3. Fāng 方 refers to a medical prescription.</p>
        </div>
